With 600,000 Mississippians considered to be food insecure, including 1 in 4 children—the highest food insecurity rate in the nation. I’ve drafted versions of HB 1343 for the last few sessions to exempt sales taxes on groceries—Republican leadership refuses to allow a floor vote.

Exciting news! The City of Jackson won one of 14 $1Million grants (out of 200 applicants!) from the Bloomberg Foundation for “Fertile Ground,” a project to promote healthy food choices and counter food insecurity in collaboration with local artists, chefs, etc. https://t.co/vJqHtUnbcd

This press conference is about Bloomberg Philanthropies’ public art challenge. As of July, Jackson was a finalist to receive $1 million for a project about food insecurity and access.
